<seg id="844">In a further examination of these business transactions, an audit group of the NKA found that in 2004 different legal regulations on the supply or acquisition of electrical energy between the Czech Republic and Germany applied.</seg>
<seg id="845">While in the Czech Republic the taxable persons declared the deliveries of electrical energy in accordance with the provisions of Law No. 235/2004 valid in 2004 as intra-Community deliveries of goods, according to the German legal provisions applicable in 2004 it was not an intra-Community purchase of goods, but taxable and taxable transactions in Germany.</seg>
<seg id="846">The differences in the legal provisions were eliminated in the Czech Republic by the adoption of Law No. 635/2004, which amended some tax provisions with effect from 1 January 2005.</seg>
<seg id="847">23. When examining intra-Community deliveries or acquisitions in cooperation with BRH, it was further established that a Czech taxable person in his ZM declared intra-Community deliveries to a German taxable person for the first and fourth quarters of 2005 with a total value of CZK 240.411.163 and another Czech taxable person in his ZM for the same period intra-Community deliveries to another German taxable person with a value of CZK 263.470.776.</seg>
<seg id="848">Information transmitted by the BRH to the NKE revealed that in both cases it had been supplies of electrical energy.</seg>
<seg id="849">According to the wording of Act No. 235/2004 in force from 1 January 2005, the place of performance for the supply of electrical energy is the place of performance where the purchaser has his legal domicile, place of business or place of business for which this delivery is made.</seg>
<seg id="850">Therefore, the Czech taxable persons should not have indicated the electricity deliveries in their ZM for 2005.</seg>
<seg id="851">The fact that both taxable persons treated the supply of electrical energy in their ZM as intra-Community deliveries led to a difference in the amount of CZK 503,881,939 in MIAS.</seg>
<seg id="852">Conclusion</seg>
<seg id="853">The cooperation has achieved the objectives of the BRH and the NKE.</seg>
<seg id="854">Both audit institutions gained in-depth knowledge of VAT management systems in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="855">The cooperation revealed differences in the two systems and in the statutory provisions governing VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="856">During the parallel tests, interesting cases of intra-Community deliveries or acquisitions came to light.</seg>
<seg id="857">For some of them, a further observation is worthwhile.</seg>
<seg id="858">On the basis of the audit results, both auditors drew up recommendations for the management of VAT.</seg>
<seg id="859">The follow-up of these recommendations in the form of a review should be part of the follow-up.</seg>
<seg id="860">The new experience and knowledge gained through the cooperation of the two audit institutions form the basis for the successful execution of future audits in the field of VAT management.</seg>
<seg id="861">Communique</seg>
<seg id="862">This report was written in Czech, English and German and signed by the President of the Supreme Control Office of the Czech Republic and the President of the Federal Audit Office of the Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
</p>
